---
description: Documentation, PHPDoc, and code comments must be written in English
alwaysApply: true
---

# English documentation and PHPDoc

- Write all project documentation in English (`README.md`, `docs/**`, `specs/**`, constitution).
- Write PHPDoc and inline code comments in English (`src/`, `tests/`, `public/`).
- Write comments in Docker/Compose/Caddy/shell and Makefile help text in English.
- Keep Twig/UI copy in English and use `lang="en"` on HTML documents.
- Do not add Spanish (or other non-English) prose to docs or PHPDoc.
- Constitution principle VI and `docs/CONTRIBUTING.md` are the source of this rule.
